      "author": "PixelAnay",
      "description": "## Fix: Input area stuck disabled after errors\n\nFixed a bug where the chat input textarea could become permanently non-editable. This happened when an error occurred during context building (before the streaming phase) — the `setStreaming(false)` call was never reached, leaving the input stuck in a disabled state.\n\n### Changes\n- Wrapped all code after `setStreaming(true)` in `sendMessage()` inside a `try/finally` block so the input is always re-enabled, even on errors\n- Reset `isStreaming` state in `onClose()` to prevent stale state when Obsidian reuses the view instance\n- Reset `isStreaming` in `onOpen()` as a safety net for view reopening",
      "draft": false,
      "name": "v5.0.29",
      "prerelease": false,
      "publishedAt": "2026-06-15T23:10:46Z",
      "tag": "5.0.29"
