      "author": "PixelAnay",
      "description": "## Engram v5.0.0\n\n> **Breaking change**: Plugin renamed from LLAMA Chat to Engram. Please reinstall via BRAT if upgrading.\n\n### What's new\n\n**Multi-provider AI support**\n- Works with any AI: local (llama.cpp, Ollama, LM Studio) or cloud (OpenAI, Claude, DeepSeek, Mistral, Groq, xAI, Gemini, OpenRouter)\n- 2 adapters cover 100% of providers (OpenAI-compatible + dedicated Anthropic adapter)\n- Switch providers from Settings with a dropdown — no config files\n\n**Persistent memory system**\n- Remembers facts about you across all sessions\n- Stored in your vault as \\Intelligence/Memory.md\\ — visible and editable\n- Auto-extracts memorable facts silently after each conversation turn\n- Use \\/memory\\ to manually trigger extraction at any time\n- Structured sections: Goals, Beliefs, Habits, Projects, Learnings, Identity\n\n**Persona system**\n- 4 built-in personas: Default, Deep Work, Journaling, Brainstorm\n- Create, edit, and delete custom personas from Settings\n- Switch instantly with \\/persona\\ or the 🎭 button in the header\n\n**Slash commands**\n- \\/memory\\ — Save facts from current conversation to memory\n- \\/forget\\ — Open memory file to edit/delete entries\n- \\/persona\\ — Switch active persona\n- \\/export\\ — Export conversation to a vault note\n- \\/clear\\ — Clear current session\n- \\/scope\\ — Show current vault access scope\n\n**Folder scope permissions**\n- Allow-list mode: restrict AI to specific folders only\n- Deny-list mode: block specific folders (previous behaviour preserved)\n- Applied at indexing, tool-call, and context levels\n\n**Cost-optimised context**\n- Memory-first: only memory + recent messages sent by default\n- Notes loaded on-demand via tools (not pre-loaded into every message)\n- Auto-inject set to 0 by default — safe for cloud APIs\n\n**Settings redesign** — 6 sections: AI Provider, Persona, Memory, Vault Access, Context & Performance, Semantic Search\n\n---\n*Install via [BRAT](https://github.com/TfTHacker/obsidian42-brat): add \\PixelAnay/localLLM_Obsidian\\*",
      "draft": false,
      "name": "5.0.0 - Engram: The AI That Remembers You",
